wikipedia_page.main: William Dean (born ca. 1882 in Australia; date of death unknown) was an Australian born English cricketer who represented Hampshire in one first-class match in 1907 against the touring South Africans. Dean took two wickets in the South Africans second innings, dismissing William Shalders LBW and Aubrey Faulkner caught and bowled.
